  "text": ". The encoders send km bits of the compressed input at each block of transmission. The first encoder transmits its source in two steps. First, it uses a fixed blocklength source-channel code [CITATION_1] with parameters ( k, n, d, γ ) . The code maps k-length blocks of the source to n-length blocks of the channel input, and the average distortion resulting from the code is less than d + γ . In this step, the encoder transmits the source in m blocks of length k. A total of nm channel uses are needed (note that n<k). In the second step, the encoder uses a large blocklength code to correct the errors in the previous step. The code has rate close to h b (γ +d) 1−h b (δ) , and its input length is equal to km.",
